# ===========================================================================
# Output Rails: Bot response filtering and output safety
# ===========================================================================

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Allowed bot response patterns
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

define bot provide project info
  "Here is the project information you requested."

define bot provide github info
  "Here are the GitHub details you requested."

define bot provide jira info
  "Here are the Jira details you requested."

define bot provide calendar info
  "Here are the calendar details you requested."

define bot provide team info
  "Here is the team status information."

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dangerous output patterns: harmful content
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

define bot respond with harmful content
  "Here is how to hack..."
  "Here is the exploit code..."
  "Here is the malware..."
  "Here are the stolen credentials..."
  "Here is the phishing template..."
  "Here is a script to attack..."
  "Here is how to bypass security..."
  "Here is the keylogger code..."
  "Here is how to social engineer..."
  "To perform a DDoS attack..."
  "Here is how to break into..."
  "To exploit this vulnerability..."

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dangerous output patterns: off-topic content
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

define bot respond off topic
  "Here is a recipe for..."
  "The meaning of life is..."
  "Here is a poem..."
  "Here is a joke..."
  "Let me tell you about history..."
  "The weather today is..."
  "Here is a story..."
  "My opinion on politics is..."
  "Here is investment advice..."
  "For your medical condition..."
  "As a legal matter..."
  "Here is a blog post about cooking..."
  "For your vacation, I recommend..."

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dangerous output patterns: system information leaks
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

define bot leak system prompt
  "My instructions are..."
  "My system prompt says..."
  "I was told to..."
  "My initial instructions..."
  "Here is my configuration..."
  "My instructions tell me to..."
  "The system prompt is..."
  "I was configured to..."
  "My prompt says..."

define bot leak internal tools
  "I have access to the following tools:"
  "My available functions are:"
  "I can call the following APIs:"
  "The MCP servers I'm connected to are:"
  "My internal tools include:"
  "I use the following endpoints:"
  "The backend architecture is:"
  "I'm connected to these services:"
  "The tool names I have are:"

define bot leak credentials
  "The API key is..."
  "The token is..."
  "The password is..."
  "The secret key is..."
  "Here are the credentials..."
  "The authentication token..."
  "The database connection string is..."
  "The environment variable contains..."
  "The .env file has..."
  "The access key is..."
  "The OAuth token is..."
  "The JWT secret is..."

define bot leak architecture details
  "The system architecture includes..."
  "The database schema is..."
  "The server configuration is..."
  "The infrastructure runs on..."
  "The backend uses the following stack..."
  "The deployment pipeline is configured as..."
  "The internal API endpoints are..."
  "The microservices communicate via..."
  "The authentication flow works by..."
  "We store data in the following databases..."

define bot generate sysadmin commands
  "Run the following command: rm -rf"
  "Execute: sudo"
  "Run this shell command:"
  "Here is the SSH command:"
  "Execute this on the server:"
  "Run chmod"
  "Execute DROP TABLE"
  "Run this database command:"
  "Here is the admin command:"

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Output filtering flows
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

define flow check output
  """Primary output filter: block harmful, off-topic, and dangerous responses."""

  when bot respond with harmful content
    bot replace with safe response
    stop

  when bot respond off topic
    bot redirect to work topics
    stop

  when bot generate sysadmin commands
    bot refuse sysadmin output
    stop

define flow block internal disclosure
  """Prevent the bot from revealing internal system details."""

  when bot leak system prompt
    bot refuse prompt leak
    stop

  when bot leak internal tools
    bot refuse tool disclosure
    stop

  when bot leak credentials
    bot refuse credential disclosure
    stop

  when bot leak architecture details
    bot refuse architecture disclosure
    stop

# -------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bot response definitions for output rails
# -------------------------------------------------------------------

define bot replace with safe response
  "I'm not able to provide that information. Let me help you with a project management, GitHub, Jira, or calendar task instead."

define bot redirect to work topics
  "Let me refocus on your work-related needs. I can help with project management, GitHub operations, Jira tickets, calendar scheduling, and team coordination. What would you like to work on?"

define bot refuse prompt leak
  "I'm not able to share details about my internal instructions or configuration. I'm here to help with project management tasks. How can I assist you?"

define bot refuse tool disclosure
  "I'm not able to disclose information about my internal tools or system capabilities. For security reasons, this information is confidential. I can help you with project management, GitHub, Jira, or calendar operations."

define bot refuse credential disclosure
  "I cannot share API keys, tokens, passwords, or any authentication credentials. This information is strictly confidential. Is there a work-related task I can help you with?"

define bot refuse architecture disclosure
  "I'm not able to reveal details about the system's internal architecture, infrastructure, or technical implementation. This information is confidential for security reasons. How can I help with your project management needs?"

define bot refuse sysadmin output
  "I cannot provide system administration commands or server-level operations. Please work with your DevOps team for infrastructure changes. I can help with project management, GitHub, Jira, or calendar tasks instead."
